---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

// Theme settings that match the main page
const theme = {
    primaryColor: "from-blue-500 to-purple-500",
    secondaryColor: "blue-600",
    accentGradient: "from-blue-500 to-purple-600",
    headingClass:
        "text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-purple-500 font-bold",
};

const currentDate = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0];
---

<Layout
    title="Privacy Policy - Luis (xLuisCumbi)"
    description="Privacy policy for Luis (xLuisCumbi) personal website, explaining our minimal data handling approach."
>
    <main class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        <h1 class={`text-4xl mb-2 text-center ${theme.headingClass}`}>
            Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-center text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
            Your privacy is important.
        </p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert mx-auto">
            <p class="text-right italic">
                <strong>Last Updated:</strong>
                {currentDate}
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                1. Introduction
            </h2>
            <p>
                This Privacy Policy explains how the personal website
                luis.cumbi.co (the "Site") handles privacy considerations. This
                is a simple, static website that does not actively collect,
                store, or process personal information from visitors.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                2. Information Collection: What We Don't Collect
            </h2>
            <p>As a static website, we do not:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 mb-4">
                <li>Use contact or newsletter forms</li>
                <li>Process or store any personal information</li>
                <li>Use user accounts or authentication</li>
                <li>Sell or share visitor information with third parties</li>
                <li>Track individual user behavior</li>
                <li>Use cookies for tracking purposes</li>
            </ul>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                3. Hosting Provider and Server Logs
            </h2>
            <p>
                This site is hosted on AWS Amplify. Like most hosting providers,
                AWS may collect standard server logs including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 mb-4">
                <li>IP addresses</li>
                <li>Browser type</li>
                <li>Access times</li>
                <li>Pages visited</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                This information is processed by AWS according to their privacy
                policy and data processing terms. This information is not
                accessed or used by us for any purpose.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                4. External Links
            </h2>
            <p>
                This website contains links to external sites, including social
                media platforms and project websites. These sites have their own
                privacy policies, and we are not responsible for their
                practices. We encourage you to read the privacy statements of
                any external sites you visit through links on our website.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                5. Local Storage
            </h2>
            <p>
                This site uses local storage only to remember your preference
                for dark or light mode. This information stays in your browser
                and is not transmitted to us or any third parties.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                6. Your Rights
            </h2>
            <p>
                Since we don't collect personal data, there is generally no
                personal information for you to access, correct, or delete.
                However, if you believe that any information related to you is
                stored on our website, feel free to contact us, and we will
                address your concern.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
            </h2>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect
                changes in technology, law, or our practices. We will notify you
                of any material changes by posting the updated Privacy Policy on
                this page with a new effective date.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-gray-800 dark:text-white"
            >
                8. Contact
            </h2>
            <p>
                If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy,
                you can contact me through any of the social media platforms
                listed on the homepage.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 text-center">
            <a
                href="/"
                class={`inline-block px-6 py-3 text-white rounded-lg transition-colors bg-gradient-to-r ${theme.primaryColor} hover:opacity-90`}
            >
                Back to Home
            </a>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
